caption.paragraph:
Figure 8. Characters of Korean 
Dusona
. A Antennal carina highly raised, rim bent upwards and with striae (
Dusona mactatoides
) B Antennal carina low and narrow, without striae (
Dusona chabarowski
) C Petiole with fine sculpture in front of strong glymma (
Dusona bicoloripes
) D Petiole without glymma (
Dusona auriculator
) E Lower valve of ovipositor straight (
Dusona koreana
) F Lower valve of ovipositor sinuous (
Dusona cultrator
). (Scale bar 0.2 mm).
